  <body>
    This java applet shows combination of two linear polarized electromagnetic 
    wave combined into a circular polarized wave propagated in the media.

    <ol>
      <li>
        Red segment represent Electric Field
      </li>
      <li>
        Blue segment represent Magnetic Field
      </li>
    </ol>
    You can modify:

    <ol>
      <li>
        T :period of the wave. =&gt; wavelength(lamda)=vy*T
      </li>
      <li>
        Ex: electric field magnitude of wave 1
      </li>
      <li>
        Ez: electric field magnitude of wave 2
      </li>
      <li>
        vy: wave velocity. =&gt; Ez/Bx=vy, where Bx is magnetic field magnitude
      </li>
    </ol>
    Please notice that E/B field are in phase when electromagnetic is travel 
    in vacuum.
  </body>
